-- U.S. Stock-Index Futures Rise on Earnings; SanDisk, Schlumberger Advance
-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 2010-10-22T11:59:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/u-s-stock-index-futures-advance-on-earnings-sandisk-schlumberger-climb.html
U.S. stock futures advanced,
signaling the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index may extend a third
straight weekly gain, as earnings improved at companies from
SanDisk Corp. to Schlumberger Ltd.  SanDisk, the largest maker of flash memory cards, rallied
4.9 percent after increasing income by shifting production to a
more efficient manufacturing technology. Schlumberger, the
biggest oilfield services provider, climbed 1.3 percent after
profit more than doubled.  Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index expiring in
December rose 0.3 percent to 1,178.9 at 7:59 a.m. in New York.
Dow Jones Industrial Average futures increased 26 points, or 0.2
percent, to 11,109.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
